Good evening, and welcome back to Wall Power. I=E2=80=99m Marion
Maneker.=C2=A0

=C2=A0

Tonight, I=E2=80=99m looking at what=E2=80=99s happening in Los Angeles fro=
m the perspective of artists and art collectors. These last few days have b=
een horrendous to watch from afar; and, while the art is hardly the first p=
riority for anyone, there are some heartbreaking and illuminating stories f=
iltering in from the evacuation zones.=C2=A0

=C2=A0

But first=E2=80=A6

* Did someone just buy a $130 million Basquiat?: The art world is filled wi=
th collector-dealers who speculate on the work of a few artists. One of the=
m is John Sayegh-Belchatowski, a French dealer who actively trades in conte=
mporary artists such as Christopher Wool, Keith Haring, and Jean-Michel Bas=
quiat. So it was serious business earlier this week when he
posted ( https://www.instagram.com/p/DEk_swVoAPt/?igsh=3DMmg3Z3FlY2toODd3&u=
